CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 21, 1959, page A18, reads: "Registering Delegates - Mrs. Helen Starkey and Mrs. Nattie Gaither, members of the two host clubs, are registering two of the many delegates who attended the Western Regional meeting of the Pennsylvania State Federation of Negro Women's Clubs. Reaching for their programs are Mrs. Mary Brooks of Washington, Pa., and Mrs. Irene Baker of Rankin. Mrs. Baker is one of the pioneer clubwomen of the Federation. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Helen Starkey and Nattie Gaither, seated, registering Mary Brooks and Irene Baker, gathered for the Western Regional meeting of the Pennsylvania State Federation of Negro Women's Clubs at the Bethlehem Baptist Church in McKeesport
